Gov. Perdue Vetoes Bill That Would Limit Access to Public Records

Gov. Bev Perdue on Thursday vetoed House Bill 104, “An Act To Clarify Legislative Confidentiality.”

“Transparency and accountability are hallmarks of my administration.  If this legislation became law, documents that are currently public record would become private,” said Perdue.  “Additionally, this bill treats certain state employees unequally.”

The General Assembly passed the legislation on August 10 after making significant changes during the last days of legislative session.

